2984static void
2985i915_gem_object_retire__read(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj, int ring)
2986{

2988
2989 RQ_BUG_ON(obj->last_read_req[ring] == NULL);
2990 RQ_BUG_ON(!(obj->active & (1 << ring)));
2991

2994
2995 if (obj->last_write_req && obj->last_write_req->ring->id == ring)
2996 i915_gem_object_retire__write(obj);
2997
2998 obj->active &= ~(1 << ring);
2999 if (obj->active)
3000 return;
3001

3003 * so that we don't steal from recently used but inactive objects
3004 * (unless we are forced to ofc!)
3005 */
3006 list_move_tail(&obj->global_list,
3007 &to_i915(obj->base.dev)->mm.bound_list);
3008

3010 if (!list_empty(&vma->mm_list))
3011 list_move_tail(&vma->mm_list, &vma->vm->inactive_list);
3012 }
3013
3014 i915_gem_request_assign(&obj->last_fenced_req, NULL);
3015 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);

3018static int
3019i915_gem_init_seqno(struct drm_device *dev, u32 seqno)
3020{
3021 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3022 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3023 int ret, i, j;
3024
3025 /* Carefully retire all requests without writing to the rings */
3026 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
3027 ret = intel_ring_idle(ring);
3028 if (ret)
3029 return ret;
3030 }
3031 i915_gem_retire_requests(dev);
3032
3033 /* Finally reset hw state */
3034 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
3035 intel_ring_init_seqno(ring, seqno);
3036
3037 for (j = 0; j < ARRAY_SIZE(ring->semaphore.sync_seqno); j++)
3038 ring->semaphore.sync_seqno[j] = 0;
3039 }

3041 return 0;

3044int i915_gem_set_seqno(struct drm_device *dev, u32 seqno)
3045{
3046 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3047 int ret;
3048
3049 if (seqno == 0)
3050 return -EINVAL;
3051
3052 /* HWS page needs to be set less than what we
3053 * will inject to ring
3054 */
3055 ret = i915_gem_init_seqno(dev, seqno - 1);
3056 if (ret)
3057 return ret;
3058
3059 /* Carefully set the last_seqno value so that wrap
3060 * detection still works
3061 */
3062 dev_priv->next_seqno = seqno;
3063 dev_priv->last_seqno = seqno - 1;
3064 if (dev_priv->last_seqno == 0)
3065 dev_priv->last_seqno--;
3066
3067 return 0;
3068}

3070int
3071i915_gem_get_seqno(struct drm_device *dev, u32 *seqno)
3072{
3073 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3074
3075 /* reserve 0 for non-seqno */
3076 if (dev_priv->next_seqno == 0) {
3077 int ret = i915_gem_init_seqno(dev, 0);
3078 if (ret)
3079 return ret;
3080
3081 dev_priv->next_seqno = 1;
3082 }
3083
3084 *seqno = dev_priv->last_seqno = dev_priv->next_seqno++;
3085 return 0;
3086}

3088/*
3089 * NB: This function is not allowed to fail. Doing so would mean the the
3090 * request is not being tracked for completion but the work itself is
3091 * going to happen on the hardware. This would be a Bad Thing(tm).
3092 */
3093void __i915_add_request(struct drm_i915_gem_request *request,
3094 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
3095 bool flush_caches)
3096{
3097 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3098 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv;
3099 struct intel_ringbuffer *ringbuf;
3100 u32 request_start;
3101 int ret;
3102
3103 if (WARN_ON(request == NULL))
3104 return;
3105
3106 ring = request->ring;
3107 dev_priv = ring->dev->dev_private;
3108 ringbuf = request->ringbuf;
3109
3110 /*
3111 * To ensure that this call will not fail, space for its emissions
3112 * should already have been reserved in the ring buffer. Let the ring
3113 * know that it is time to use that space up.
3114 */
3115 intel_ring_reserved_space_use(ringbuf);
3116
3117 request_start = intel_ring_get_tail(ringbuf);
3118 /*
3119 * Emit any outstanding flushes - execbuf can fail to emit the flush
3120 * after having emitted the batchbuffer command. Hence we need to fix
3121 * things up similar to emitting the lazy request. The difference here
3122 * is that the flush _must_ happen before the next request, no matter
3123 * what.
3124 */
3125 if (flush_caches) {
3126 if (i915.enable_execlists)
3127 ret = logical_ring_flush_all_caches(request);
3128 else
3129 ret = intel_ring_flush_all_caches(request);
3130 /* Not allowed to fail! */
3131 WARN(ret, "*_ring_flush_all_caches failed: %d!\n", ret);
3132 }
3133
3134 /* Record the position of the start of the request so that
3135 * should we detect the updated seqno part-way through the
3136 * GPU processing the request, we never over-estimate the
3137 * position of the head.
3138 */
3139 request->postfix = intel_ring_get_tail(ringbuf);
3140
3141 if (i915.enable_execlists)
3142 ret = ring->emit_request(request);
3143 else {
3144 ret = ring->add_request(request);
3145
3146 request->tail = intel_ring_get_tail(ringbuf);
3147 }
3148 /* Not allowed to fail! */
3149 WARN(ret, "emit|add_request failed: %d!\n", ret);
3150
3151 request->head = request_start;
3152
3153 /* Whilst this request exists, batch_obj will be on the
3154 * active_list, and so will hold the active reference. Only when this
3155 * request is retired will the the batch_obj be moved onto the
3156 * inactive_list and lose its active reference. Hence we do not need
3157 * to explicitly hold another reference here.
3158 */
3159 request->batch_obj = obj;
3160
3161 request->emitted_jiffies = jiffies;
3162 request->previous_seqno = ring->last_submitted_seqno;
3163 ring->last_submitted_seqno = request->seqno;
3164 list_add_tail(&request->list, &ring->request_list);
3165
3166 trace_i915_gem_request_add(request);
3167
3168 i915_queue_hangcheck(ring->dev);
3169
3170 queue_delayed_work(dev_priv->wq,
3171 &dev_priv->mm.retire_work,
3172 round_jiffies_up_relative(HZ));
3173 intel_mark_busy(dev_priv->dev);
3174
3175 /* Sanity check that the reserved size was large enough. */
3176 intel_ring_reserved_space_end(ringbuf);
3177}

3179static bool i915_context_is_banned(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
3180 const struct intel_context *ctx)
3181{
3182 unsigned long elapsed;
3183
3184 elapsed = get_seconds() - ctx->hang_stats.guilty_ts;
3185
3186 if (ctx->hang_stats.banned)
3187 return true;
3188
3189 if (ctx->hang_stats.ban_period_seconds &&
3190 elapsed <= ctx->hang_stats.ban_period_seconds) {
3191 if (!i915_gem_context_is_default(ctx)) {
3192 DRM_DEBUG("context hanging too fast, banning!\n");
3193 return true;
3194 } else if (i915_stop_ring_allow_ban(dev_priv)) {
3195 if (i915_stop_ring_allow_warn(dev_priv))
3196 DRM_ERROR("gpu hanging too fast, banning!\n");
3197 return true;
3198 }
3199 }
3200
3201 return false;
3202}

3253 if (!req_out)

3351static void i915_gem_reset_ring_cleanup(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
3352 struct intel_engine_cs *ring)
3353{
3354 while (!list_empty(&ring->active_list)) {
3355 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
3356
3357 obj = list_first_entry(&ring->active_list,
3358 struct drm_i915_gem_object,
3359 ring_list[ring->id]);
3360
3361 i915_gem_object_retire__read(obj, ring->id);
3362 }
3363
3364 /*
3365 * Clear the execlists queue up before freeing the requests, as those
3366 * are the ones that keep the context and ringbuffer backing objects
3367 * pinned in place.
3368 */
3369 while (!list_empty(&ring->execlist_queue)) {
3370 struct drm_i915_gem_request *submit_req;
3371
3372 submit_req = list_first_entry(&ring->execlist_queue,
3373 struct drm_i915_gem_request,
3374 execlist_link);
3375 list_del(&submit_req->execlist_link);
3376
3377 if (submit_req->ctx != ring->default_context)
3378 intel_lr_context_unpin(submit_req);
3379
3380 i915_gem_request_unreference(submit_req);
3381 }
3382
3383 /*
3384 * We must free the requests after all the corresponding objects have
3385 * been moved off active lists. Which is the same order as the normal
3386 * retire_requests function does. This is important if object hold
3387 * implicit references on things like e.g. ppgtt address spaces through
3388 * the request.
3389 */
3390 while (!list_empty(&ring->request_list)) {
3391 struct drm_i915_gem_request *request;
3392
3393 request = list_first_entry(&ring->request_list,
3394 struct drm_i915_gem_request,
3395 list);
3396
3397 i915_gem_request_retire(request);
3398 }

3401void i915_gem_reset(struct drm_device *dev)
3402{

3404 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3405 int i;
3406

3408 * Before we free the objects from the requests, we need to inspect
3409 * them for finding the guilty party. As the requests only borrow
3410 * their reference to the objects, the inspection must be done first.
3411 */

3425/**
3426 * This function clears the request list as sequence numbers are passed.
3427 */
3428void
3429i915_gem_retire_requests_ring(struct intel_engine_cs *ring)
3430{
3431 WARN_ON(i915_verify_lists(ring->dev));
3432
3433 /* Retire requests first as we use it above for the early return.
3434 * If we retire requests last, we may use a later seqno and so clear
3435 * the requests lists without clearing the active list, leading to
3436 * confusion.
3437 */
3438 while (!list_empty(&ring->request_list)) {
3439 struct drm_i915_gem_request *request;
3440
3441 request = list_first_entry(&ring->request_list,
3442 struct drm_i915_gem_request,
3443 list);
3444
3445 if (!i915_gem_request_completed(request, true))
3446 break;
3447
3448 i915_gem_request_retire(request);
3449 }
3450
3451 /* Move any buffers on the active list that are no longer referenced
3452 * by the ringbuffer to the flushing/inactive lists as appropriate,
3453 * before we free the context associated with the requests.
3454 */
3455 while (!list_empty(&ring->active_list)) {
3456 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
3457
3458 obj = list_first_entry(&ring->active_list,
3459 struct drm_i915_gem_object,
3460 ring_list[ring->id]);
3461
3462 if (!list_empty(&obj->last_read_req[ring->id]->list))
3463 break;
3464
3465 i915_gem_object_retire__read(obj, ring->id);
3466 }
3467
3468 if (unlikely(ring->trace_irq_req &&
3469 i915_gem_request_completed(ring->trace_irq_req, true))) {
3470 ring->irq_put(ring);
3471 i915_gem_request_assign(&ring->trace_irq_req, NULL);
3472 }
3473
3474 WARN_ON(i915_verify_lists(ring->dev));
3475}
3476
3477bool
3478i915_gem_retire_requests(struct drm_device *dev)
3479{
3480 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3481 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3482 bool idle = true;
3483 int i;
3484
3485 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
3486 i915_gem_retire_requests_ring(ring);
3487 idle &= list_empty(&ring->request_list);
3488 if (i915.enable_execlists) {
3489 unsigned long flags;
3490
3491 spin_lock_irqsave(&ring->execlist_lock, flags);
3492 idle &= list_empty(&ring->execlist_queue);
3493 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ring->execlist_lock, flags);
3494
3495 intel_execlists_retire_requests(ring);
3496 }
3497 }
3498
3499 if (idle)
3500 mod_delayed_work(dev_priv->wq,
3501 &dev_priv->mm.idle_work,
3502 msecs_to_jiffies(100));
3503
3504 return idle;
3505}
3506
3507static void
3508i915_gem_retire_work_handler(struct work_struct *work)
3509{
3510 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv =
3511 container_of(work, typeof(*dev_priv), mm.retire_work.work);
3512 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
3513 bool idle;
3514
3515 /* Come back later if the device is busy... */
3516 idle = false;
3517 if (mutex_trylock(&dev->struct_mutex)) {
3518 idle = i915_gem_retire_requests(dev);
3519 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
3520 }
3521 if (!idle)
3522 queue_delayed_work(dev_priv->wq, &dev_priv->mm.retire_work,
3523 round_jiffies_up_relative(HZ));
3524}

3526static void
3527i915_gem_idle_work_handler(struct work_struct *work)
3528{
3529 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv =
3530 container_of(work, typeof(*dev_priv), mm.idle_work.work);
3531 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
3532 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3533 int i;
3534
3535 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i)
3536 if (!list_empty(&ring->request_list))
3537 return;
3538
3539 intel_mark_idle(dev);
3540
3541 if (mutex_trylock(&dev->struct_mutex)) {
3542 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3543 int i;
3544
3545 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i)
3546 i915_gem_batch_pool_fini(&ring->batch_pool);
3547
3548 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
3549 }
3550}

3552/**
3553 * Ensures that an object will eventually get non-busy by flushing any required
3554 * write domains, emitting any outstanding lazy request and retiring and
3555 * completed requests.
3556 */
3557static int
3558i915_gem_object_flush_active(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj)
3559{
3560 int i;
3561
3562 if (!obj->active)
3563 return 0;
3564
3565 for (i = 0; i < I915_NUM_RINGS; i++) {
3566 struct drm_i915_gem_request *req;
3567
3568 req = obj->last_read_req[i];
3569 if (req == NULL)
3570 continue;
3571
3572 if (list_empty(&req->list))
3573 goto retire;
3574
3575 if (i915_gem_request_completed(req, true)) {
3576 __i915_gem_request_retire__upto(req);
3577retire:
3578 i915_gem_object_retire__read(obj, i);
3579 }
3580 }
3581
3582 return 0;
3583}

3585/**
3586 * i915_gem_wait_ioctl - implements DRM_IOCTL_I915_GEM_WAIT
3587 * @DRM_IOCTL_ARGS: standard ioctl arguments
3588 *
3589 * Returns 0 if successful, else an error is returned with the remaining time in
3590 * the timeout parameter.
3591 * -ETIME: object is still busy after timeout
3592 * -ERESTARTSYS: signal interrupted the wait
3593 * -ENONENT: object doesn't exist
3594 * Also possible, but rare:
3595 * -EAGAIN: GPU wedged
3596 * -ENOMEM: damn
3597 * -ENODEV: Internal IRQ fail
3598 * -E?: The add request failed
3599 *
3600 * The wait ioctl with a timeout of 0 reimplements the busy ioctl. With any
3601 * non-zero timeout parameter the wait ioctl will wait for the given number of
3602 * nanoseconds on an object becoming unbusy. Since the wait itself does so
3603 * without holding struct_mutex the object may become re-busied before this
3604 * function completes. A similar but shorter * race condition exists in the busy
3605 * ioctl
3606 */
3607int
3608i915_gem_wait_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data, struct drm_file *file)
3609{
3610 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3611 struct drm_i915_gem_wait *args = data;
3612 struct drm_gem_object *gobj;
3613 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
3614 struct drm_i915_gem_request *req[I915_NUM_RINGS];
3615 unsigned reset_counter;
3616 int i, n = 0;
3617 int ret;
3618
3619 if (args->flags != 0)
3620 return -EINVAL;
3621
3622 ret = i915_mutex_lock_interruptible(dev);
3623 if (ret)
3624 return ret;
3625
3626 gobj = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file, args->bo_handle);
3627 if (gobj == NULL) {
3628 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
3629 return -ENOENT;
3630 }
3631 obj = to_intel_bo(gobj);
3632
3633 /* Need to make sure the object gets inactive eventually. */
3634 ret = i915_gem_object_flush_active(obj);
3635 if (ret)
3636 goto out;
3637
3638 if (!obj->active)
3639 goto out;
3640
3641 /* Do this after OLR check to make sure we make forward progress polling
3642 * on this IOCTL with a timeout == 0 (like busy ioctl)
3643 */
3644 if (args->timeout_ns == 0) {
3645 ret = -ETIME;
3646 goto out;
3647 }
3648
3649 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
3650 reset_counter = atomic_read(&dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_counter);
3651
3652 for (i = 0; i < I915_NUM_RINGS; i++) {
3653 if (obj->last_read_req[i] == NULL)
3654 continue;
3655
3656 req[n++] = i915_gem_request_reference(obj->last_read_req[i]);
3657 }
3658
3659 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
3660
3661 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3662 if (ret == 0)
3663 ret = __i915_wait_request(req[i], reset_counter, true,
3664 args->timeout_ns > 0 ? &args->timeout_ns : NULL,
3665 file->driver_priv);
3666 i915_gem_request_unreference__unlocked(req[i]);
3667 }
3668 return ret;
3669
3670out:
3671 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
3672 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
3673 return ret;
3674}
3675
3676static int
3677__i915_gem_object_sync(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
3678 struct intel_engine_cs *to,
3679 struct drm_i915_gem_request *from_req,
3680 struct drm_i915_gem_request **to_req)
3681{
3682 struct intel_engine_cs *from;
3683 int ret;
3684
3685 from = i915_gem_request_get_ring(from_req);
3686 if (to == from)
3687 return 0;
3688
3689 if (i915_gem_request_completed(from_req, true))
3690 return 0;
3691
3692 if (!i915_semaphore_is_enabled(obj->base.dev)) {
3693 struct drm_i915_private *i915 = to_i915(obj->base.dev);
3694 ret = __i915_wait_request(from_req,
3695 atomic_read(&i915->gpu_error.reset_counter),
3696 i915->mm.interruptible,
3697 NULL,
3698 &i915->rps.semaphores);
3699 if (ret)
3700 return ret;
3701
3702 i915_gem_object_retire_request(obj, from_req);
3703 } else {
3704 int idx = intel_ring_sync_index(from, to);
3705 u32 seqno = i915_gem_request_get_seqno(from_req);
3706
3707 WARN_ON(!to_req);
3708
3709 if (seqno <= from->semaphore.sync_seqno[idx])
3710 return 0;
3711
3712 if (*to_req == NULL) {
3713 ret = i915_gem_request_alloc(to, to->default_context, to_req);
3714 if (ret)
3715 return ret;
3716 }
3717
3718 trace_i915_gem_ring_sync_to(*to_req, from, from_req);
3719 ret = to->semaphore.sync_to(*to_req, from, seqno);
3720 if (ret)
3721 return ret;
3722
3723 /* We use last_read_req because sync_to()
3724 * might have just caused seqno wrap under
3725 * the radar.
3726 */
3727 from->semaphore.sync_seqno[idx] =
3728 i915_gem_request_get_seqno(obj->last_read_req[from->id]);
3729 }
3730
3731 return 0;
3732}
3733
3734/**
3735 * i915_gem_object_sync - sync an object to a ring.
3736 *
3737 * @obj: object which may be in use on another ring.
3738 * @to: ring we wish to use the object on. May be NULL.
3739 * @to_req: request we wish to use the object for. See below.
3740 * This will be allocated and returned if a request is
3741 * required but not passed in.
3742 *
3743 * This code is meant to abstract object synchronization with the GPU.
3744 * Calling with NULL implies synchronizing the object with the CPU
3745 * rather than a particular GPU ring. Conceptually we serialise writes
3746 * between engines inside the GPU. We only allow one engine to write
3747 * into a buffer at any time, but multiple readers. To ensure each has
3748 * a coherent view of memory, we must:
3749 *
3750 * - If there is an outstanding write request to the object, the new
3751 * request must wait for it to complete (either CPU or in hw, requests
3752 * on the same ring will be naturally ordered).
3753 *
3754 * - If we are a write request (pending_write_domain is set), the new
3755 * request must wait for outstanding read requests to complete.
3756 *
3757 * For CPU synchronisation (NULL to) no request is required. For syncing with
3758 * rings to_req must be non-NULL. However, a request does not have to be
3759 * pre-allocated. If *to_req is NULL and sync commands will be emitted then a
3760 * request will be allocated automatically and returned through *to_req. Note
3761 * that it is not guaranteed that commands will be emitted (because the system
3762 * might already be idle). Hence there is no need to create a request that
3763 * might never have any work submitted. Note further that if a request is
3764 * returned in *to_req, it is the responsibility of the caller to submit
3765 * that request (after potentially adding more work to it).
3766 *
3767 * Returns 0 if successful, else propagates up the lower layer error.
3768 */
3769int
3770i915_gem_object_sync(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
3771 struct intel_engine_cs *to,
3772 struct drm_i915_gem_request **to_req)
3773{
3774 const bool readonly = obj->base.pending_write_domain == 0;
3775 struct drm_i915_gem_request *req[I915_NUM_RINGS];
3776 int ret, i, n;
3777
3778 if (!obj->active)
3779 return 0;
3780
3781 if (to == NULL)
3782 return i915_gem_object_wait_rendering(obj, readonly);
3783
3784 n = 0;
3785 if (readonly) {
3786 if (obj->last_write_req)
3787 req[n++] = obj->last_write_req;
3788 } else {
3789 for (i = 0; i < I915_NUM_RINGS; i++)
3790 if (obj->last_read_req[i])
3791 req[n++] = obj->last_read_req[i];
3792 }
3793 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3794 ret = __i915_gem_object_sync(obj, to, req[i], to_req);
3795 if (ret)
3796 return ret;
3797 }
3798
3799 return 0;
3800}
3801
3802static void i915_gem_object_finish_gtt(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj)
3803{
3804 u32 old_write_domain, old_read_domains;
3805
3806 /* Force a pagefault for domain tracking on next user access */
3807 i915_gem_release_mmap(obj);
3808
3809 if ((obj->base.read_domains & I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT) == 0)
3810 return;
3811
3812 /* Wait for any direct GTT access to complete */
3813 mb();
3814
3815 old_read_domains = obj->base.read_domains;
3816 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
3817
3818 obj->base.read_domains &= ~I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
3819 obj->base.write_domain &= ~I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
3820
3821 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
3822 old_read_domains,
3823 old_write_domain);
3824}

3826static int __i915_vma_unbind(struct i915_vma *vma, bool wait)
3827{
3828 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj = vma->obj;
3829 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = obj->base.dev->dev_private;
3830 int ret;
3831
3832 if (list_empty(&vma->vma_link))
3833 return 0;
3834
3835 if (!drm_mm_node_allocated(&vma->node)) {
3836 i915_gem_vma_destroy(vma);
3837 return 0;
3838 }
3839
3840 if (vma->pin_count)
3841 return -EBUSY;
3842
3843 BUG_ON(obj->pages == NULL);
3844
3845 if (wait) {
3846 ret = i915_gem_object_wait_rendering(obj, false);
3847 if (ret)
3848 return ret;
3849 }
3850
3851 if (i915_is_ggtt(vma->vm) &&
3852 vma->ggtt_view.type == I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL) {
3853 i915_gem_object_finish_gtt(obj);
3854
3855 /* release the fence reg _after_ flushing */
3856 ret = i915_gem_object_put_fence(obj);
3857 if (ret)
3858 return ret;
3859 }
3860
3861 trace_i915_vma_unbind(vma);
3862
3863 vma->vm->unbind_vma(vma);
3864 vma->bound = 0;
3865
3866 list_del_init(&vma->mm_list);
3867 if (i915_is_ggtt(vma->vm)) {
3868 if (vma->ggtt_view.type == I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL) {
3869 obj->map_and_fenceable = false;
3870 } else if (vma->ggtt_view.pages) {
3871#ifdef __NetBSD__
3872 panic("rotated/partial views can't happen");
3873#else
3874 sg_free_table(vma->ggtt_view.pages);
3875 kfree(vma->ggtt_view.pages);
3876#endif
3877 }
3878 vma->ggtt_view.pages = NULL;
3879 }
3880
3881 drm_mm_remove_node(&vma->node);
3882 i915_gem_vma_destroy(vma);
3883
3884 /* Since the unbound list is global, only move to that list if
3885 * no more VMAs exist. */
3886 if (list_empty(&obj->vma_list))
3887 list_move_tail(&obj->global_list, &dev_priv->mm.unbound_list);
3888
3889 /* And finally now the object is completely decoupled from this vma,
3890 * we can drop its hold on the backing storage and allow it to be
3891 * reaped by the shrinker.
3892 */
3893 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
3894
3895 return 0;
3896}

3898int i915_vma_unbind(struct i915_vma *vma)
3899{
3900 return __i915_vma_unbind(vma, true);
3901}
3902
3903int __i915_vma_unbind_no_wait(struct i915_vma *vma)
3904{
3905 return __i915_vma_unbind(vma, false);
3906}

3908int i915_gpu_idle(struct drm_device *dev)
3909{
3910 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3911 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
3912 int ret, i;
3913
3914 /* Flush everything onto the inactive list. */
3915 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
3916 if (!i915.enable_execlists) {
3917 struct drm_i915_gem_request *req;
3918
3919 ret = i915_gem_request_alloc(ring, ring->default_context, &req);
3920 if (ret)
3921 return ret;
3922
3923 ret = i915_switch_context(req);
3924 if (ret) {
3925 i915_gem_request_cancel(req);
3926 return ret;
3927 }
3928
3929 i915_add_request_no_flush(req);
3930 }
3931
3932 ret = intel_ring_idle(ring);
3933 if (ret)
3934 return ret;
3935 }
3936
3937 WARN_ON(i915_verify_lists(dev));
3938 return 0;
3939}

3941static bool i915_gem_valid_gtt_space(struct i915_vma *vma,
3942 unsigned long cache_level)
3943{
3944 struct drm_mm_node *gtt_space = &vma->node;
3945 struct drm_mm_node *other;
3946
3947 /*
3948 * On some machines we have to be careful when putting differing types
3949 * of snoopable memory together to avoid the prefetcher crossing memory
3950 * domains and dying. During vm initialisation, we decide whether or not
3951 * these constraints apply and set the drm_mm.color_adjust
3952 * appropriately.
3953 */
3954 if (vma->vm->mm.color_adjust == NULL)
3955 return true;
3956
3957 if (!drm_mm_node_allocated(gtt_space))
3958 return true;
3959
3960 if (list_empty(&gtt_space->node_list))
3961 return true;
3962
3963 other = list_entry(gtt_space->node_list.prev, struct drm_mm_node, node_list);
3964 if (other->allocated && !other->hole_follows && other->color != cache_level)
3965 return false;
3966
3967 other = list_entry(gtt_space->node_list.next, struct drm_mm_node, node_list);
3968 if (other->allocated && !gtt_space->hole_follows && other->color != cache_level)
3969 return false;
3970
3971 return true;
3972}
3973
3974/**
3975 * Finds free space in the GTT aperture and binds the object or a view of it
3976 * there.
3977 */
3978static struct i915_vma *
3979i915_gem_object_bind_to_vm(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
3980 struct i915_address_space *vm,
3981 const struct i915_ggtt_view *ggtt_view,
3982 unsigned alignment,
3983 uint64_t flags)
3984{
3985 struct drm_device *dev = obj->base.dev;
3986 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3987 u32 fence_alignment, unfenced_alignment;
3988 u32 search_flag, alloc_flag;
3989 u64 start, end;
3990 u64 size, fence_size;
3991 struct i915_vma *vma;
3992 int ret;
3993
3994 if (i915_is_ggtt(vm)) {
3995 u32 view_size;
3996
3997 if (WARN_ON(!ggtt_view))
3998 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
3999
4000 view_size = i915_ggtt_view_size(obj, ggtt_view);
4001
4002 fence_size = i915_gem_get_gtt_size(dev,
4003 view_size,
4004 obj->tiling_mode);
4005 fence_alignment = i915_gem_get_gtt_alignment(dev,
4006 view_size,
4007 obj->tiling_mode,
4008 true);
4009 unfenced_alignment = i915_gem_get_gtt_alignment(dev,
4010 view_size,
4011 obj->tiling_mode,
4012 false);
4013 size = flags & PIN_MAPPABLE ? fence_size : view_size;
4014 } else {
4015 fence_size = i915_gem_get_gtt_size(dev,
4016 obj->base.size,
4017 obj->tiling_mode);
4018 fence_alignment = i915_gem_get_gtt_alignment(dev,
4019 obj->base.size,
4020 obj->tiling_mode,
4021 true);
4022 unfenced_alignment =
4023 i915_gem_get_gtt_alignment(dev,
4024 obj->base.size,
4025 obj->tiling_mode,
4026 false);
4027 size = flags & PIN_MAPPABLE ? fence_size : obj->base.size;
4028 }
4029
4030 start = flags & PIN_OFFSET_BIAS ? flags & PIN_OFFSET_MASK : 0;
4031 end = vm->total;
4032 if (flags & PIN_MAPPABLE)
4033 end = min_t(u64, end, dev_priv->gtt.mappable_end);
4034 if (flags & PIN_ZONE_4G)
4035 end = min_t(u64, end, (1ULL << 32));
4036
4037 if (alignment == 0)
4038 alignment = flags & PIN_MAPPABLE ? fence_alignment :
4039 unfenced_alignment;
4040 if (flags & PIN_MAPPABLE && alignment & (fence_alignment - 1)) {
4041 DRM_DEBUG("Invalid object (view type=%u) alignment requested %u\n",
4042 ggtt_view ? ggtt_view->type : 0,
4043 alignment);
4044 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
4045 }
4046
4047 /* If binding the object/GGTT view requires more space than the entire
4048 * aperture has, reject it early before evicting everything in a vain
4049 * attempt to find space.
4050 */
4051 if (size > end) {
4052 DRM_DEBUG("Attempting to bind an object (view type=%u) larger than the aperture: size=%"PRIx64" > %s aperture=%"PRIx64"\n",
4053 ggtt_view ? ggtt_view->type : 0,
4054 size,
4055 flags & PIN_MAPPABLE ? "mappable" : "total",
4056 end);
4057 return ERR_PTR(-E2BIG);
4058 }
4059
4060 ret = i915_gem_object_get_pages(obj);
4061 if (ret)
4062 return ERR_PTR(ret);
4063
4064 i915_gem_object_pin_pages(obj);
4065
4066 vma = ggtt_view ? i915_gem_obj_lookup_or_create_ggtt_vma(obj, ggtt_view) :
4067 i915_gem_obj_lookup_or_create_vma(obj, vm);
4068
4069 if (IS_ERR(vma))
4070 goto err_unpin;
4071
4072 if (flags & PIN_HIGH) {
4073 search_flag = DRM_MM_SEARCH_BELOW;
4074 alloc_flag = DRM_MM_CREATE_TOP;
4075 } else {
4076 search_flag = DRM_MM_SEARCH_DEFAULT;
4077 alloc_flag = DRM_MM_CREATE_DEFAULT;
4078 }
4079
4080search_free:
4081 ret = drm_mm_insert_node_in_range_generic(&vm->mm, &vma->node,
4082 size, alignment,
4083 obj->cache_level,
4084 start, end,
4085 search_flag,
4086 alloc_flag);
4087 if (ret) {
4088 ret = i915_gem_evict_something(dev, vm, size, alignment,
4089 obj->cache_level,
4090 start, end,
4091 flags);
4092 if (ret == 0)
4093 goto search_free;
4094
4095 goto err_free_vma;
4096 }
4097 if (WARN_ON(!i915_gem_valid_gtt_space(vma, obj->cache_level))) {
4098 ret = -EINVAL;
4099 goto err_remove_node;
4100 }
4101
4102 trace_i915_vma_bind(vma, flags);
4103 ret = i915_vma_bind(vma, obj->cache_level, flags);
4104 if (ret)
4105 goto err_remove_node;
4106
4107 list_move_tail(&obj->global_list, &dev_priv->mm.bound_list);
4108 list_add_tail(&vma->mm_list, &vm->inactive_list);
4109
4110 return vma;
4111
4112err_remove_node:
4113 drm_mm_remove_node(&vma->node);
4114err_free_vma:
4115 i915_gem_vma_destroy(vma);
4116 vma = ERR_PTR(ret);
4117err_unpin:
4118 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
4119 return vma;
4120}
4121
4122bool
4123i915_gem_clflush_object(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4124 bool force)
4125{
4126 /* If we don't have a page list set up, then we're not pinned
4127 * to GPU, and we can ignore the cache flush because it'll happen
4128 * again at bind time.
4129 */
4130 if (obj->pages == NULL)
4131 return false;
4132
4133 /*
4134 * Stolen memory is always coherent with the GPU as it is explicitly
4135 * marked as wc by the system, or the system is cache-coherent.
4136 */
4137 if (obj->stolen || obj->phys_handle)
4138 return false;
4139
4140 /* If the GPU is snooping the contents of the CPU cache,
4141 * we do not need to manually clear the CPU cache lines. However,
4142 * the caches are only snooped when the render cache is
4143 * flushed/invalidated. As we always have to emit invalidations
4144 * and flushes when moving into and out of the RENDER domain, correct
4145 * snooping behaviour occurs naturally as the result of our domain
4146 * tracking.
4147 */
4148 if (!force && cpu_cache_is_coherent(obj->base.dev, obj->cache_level)) {
4149 obj->cache_dirty = true;
4150 return false;
4151 }
4152
4153 trace_i915_gem_object_clflush(obj);
4154#ifdef __NetBSD__
4155 drm_clflush_pglist(&obj->pageq);
4156#else
4157 drm_clflush_sg(obj->pages);
4158#endif
4159 obj->cache_dirty = false;
4160
4161 return true;
4162}
4163
4164/** Flushes the GTT write domain for the object if it's dirty. */
4165static void
4166i915_gem_object_flush_gtt_write_domain(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj)
4167{
4168 uint32_t old_write_domain;
4169
4170 if (obj->base.write_domain != I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT)
4171 return;
4172
4173 /* No actual flushing is required for the GTT write domain. Writes
4174 * to it immediately go to main memory as far as we know, so there's
4175 * no chipset flush. It also doesn't land in render cache.
4176 *
4177 * However, we do have to enforce the order so that all writes through
4178 * the GTT land before any writes to the device, such as updates to
4179 * the GATT itself.
4180 */
4181 wmb();
4182
4183 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
4184 obj->base.write_domain = 0;
4185
4186 intel_fb_obj_flush(obj, false, ORIGIN_GTT);
4187
4188 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
4189 obj->base.read_domains,
4190 old_write_domain);
4191}
4192
4193/** Flushes the CPU write domain for the object if it's dirty. */
4194static void
4195i915_gem_object_flush_cpu_write_domain(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj)
4196{
4197 uint32_t old_write_domain;
4198
4199 if (obj->base.write_domain != I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU)
4200 return;
4201
4202 if (i915_gem_clflush_object(obj, obj->pin_display))
4203 i915_gem_chipset_flush(obj->base.dev);
4204
4205 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
4206 obj->base.write_domain = 0;
4207
4208 intel_fb_obj_flush(obj, false, ORIGIN_CPU);
4209
4210 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
4211 obj->base.read_domains,
4212 old_write_domain);
4213}
4214
4215/**
4216 * Moves a single object to the GTT read, and possibly write domain.
4217 *
4218 * This function returns when the move is complete, including waiting on
4219 * flushes to occur.
4220 */
4221int
4222i915_gem_object_set_to_gtt_domain(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj, bool write)
4223{
4224 uint32_t old_write_domain, old_read_domains;
4225 struct i915_vma *vma;
4226 int ret;
4227
4228 if (obj->base.write_domain == I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT)
4229 return 0;
4230
4231 ret = i915_gem_object_wait_rendering(obj, !write);
4232 if (ret)
4233 return ret;
4234
4235 /* Flush and acquire obj->pages so that we are coherent through
4236 * direct access in memory with previous cached writes through
4237 * shmemfs and that our cache domain tracking remains valid.
4238 * For example, if the obj->filp was moved to swap without us
4239 * being notified and releasing the pages, we would mistakenly
4240 * continue to assume that the obj remained out of the CPU cached
4241 * domain.
4242 */
4243 ret = i915_gem_object_get_pages(obj);
4244 if (ret)
4245 return ret;
4246
4247 i915_gem_object_flush_cpu_write_domain(obj);
4248
4249 /* Serialise direct access to this object with the barriers for
4250 * coherent writes from the GPU, by effectively invalidating the
4251 * GTT domain upon first access.
4252 */
4253 if ((obj->base.read_domains & I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT) == 0)
4254 mb();
4255
4256 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
4257 old_read_domains = obj->base.read_domains;
4258
4259 /* It should now be out of any other write domains, and we can update
4260 * the domain values for our changes.
4261 */
4262 BUG_ON((obj->base.write_domain & ~I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT) != 0);
4263 obj->base.read_domains |= I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
4264 if (write) {
4265 obj->base.read_domains = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
4266 obj->base.write_domain = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
4267 obj->dirty = 1;
4268 }
4269
4270 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
4271 old_read_domains,
4272 old_write_domain);
4273
4274 /* And bump the LRU for this access */
4275 vma = i915_gem_obj_to_ggtt(obj);
4276 if (vma && drm_mm_node_allocated(&vma->node) && !obj->active)
4277 list_move_tail(&vma->mm_list,
4278 &to_i915(obj->base.dev)->gtt.base.inactive_list);
4279
4280 return 0;
4281}

4283/**
4284 * Changes the cache-level of an object across all VMA.
4285 *
4286 * After this function returns, the object will be in the new cache-level
4287 * across all GTT and the contents of the backing storage will be coherent,
4288 * with respect to the new cache-level. In order to keep the backing storage
4289 * coherent for all users, we only allow a single cache level to be set
4290 * globally on the object and prevent it from being changed whilst the
4291 * hardware is reading from the object. That is if the object is currently
4292 * on the scanout it will be set to uncached (or equivalent display
4293 * cache coherency) and all non-MOCS GPU access will also be uncached so
4294 * that all direct access to the scanout remains coherent.
4295 */
4296int i915_gem_object_set_cache_level(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4297 enum i915_cache_level cache_level)
4298{
4299 struct drm_device *dev = obj->base.dev;
4300 struct i915_vma *vma, *next;
4301 bool bound = false;
4302 int ret = 0;
4303
4304 if (obj->cache_level == cache_level)
4305 goto out;
4306
4307 /* Inspect the list of currently bound VMA and unbind any that would
4308 * be invalid given the new cache-level. This is principally to
4309 * catch the issue of the CS prefetch crossing page boundaries and
4310 * reading an invalid PTE on older architectures.
4311 */
4312 list_for_each_entry_safe(vma, next, &obj->vma_list, vma_link) {
4313 if (!drm_mm_node_allocated(&vma->node))
4314 continue;
4315
4316 if (vma->pin_count) {
4317 DRM_DEBUG("can not change the cache level of pinned objects\n");
4318 return -EBUSY;
4319 }
4320
4321 if (!i915_gem_valid_gtt_space(vma, cache_level)) {
4322 ret = i915_vma_unbind(vma);
4323 if (ret)
4324 return ret;
4325 } else
4326 bound = true;
4327 }
4328
4329 /* We can reuse the existing drm_mm nodes but need to change the
4330 * cache-level on the PTE. We could simply unbind them all and
4331 * rebind with the correct cache-level on next use. However since
4332 * we already have a valid slot, dma mapping, pages etc, we may as
4333 * rewrite the PTE in the belief that doing so tramples upon less
4334 * state and so involves less work.
4335 */
4336 if (bound) {
4337 /* Before we change the PTE, the GPU must not be accessing it.
4338 * If we wait upon the object, we know that all the bound
4339 * VMA are no longer active.
4340 */
4341 ret = i915_gem_object_wait_rendering(obj, false);
4342 if (ret)
4343 return ret;
4344
4345 if (!HAS_LLC(dev) && cache_level != I915_CACHE_NONE) {
4346 /* Access to snoopable pages through the GTT is
4347 * incoherent and on some machines causes a hard
4348 * lockup. Relinquish the CPU mmaping to force
4349 * userspace to refault in the pages and we can
4350 * then double check if the GTT mapping is still
4351 * valid for that pointer access.
4352 */
4353 i915_gem_release_mmap(obj);
4354
4355 /* As we no longer need a fence for GTT access,
4356 * we can relinquish it now (and so prevent having
4357 * to steal a fence from someone else on the next
4358 * fence request). Note GPU activity would have
4359 * dropped the fence as all snoopable access is
4360 * supposed to be linear.
4361 */
4362 ret = i915_gem_object_put_fence(obj);
4363 if (ret)
4364 return ret;
4365 } else {
4366 /* We either have incoherent backing store and
4367 * so no GTT access or the architecture is fully
4368 * coherent. In such cases, existing GTT mmaps
4369 * ignore the cache bit in the PTE and we can
4370 * rewrite it without confusing the GPU or having
4371 * to force userspace to fault back in its mmaps.
4372 */
4373 }
4374
4375 list_for_each_entry(vma, &obj->vma_list, vma_link) {
4376 if (!drm_mm_node_allocated(&vma->node))
4377 continue;
4378
4379 ret = i915_vma_bind(vma, cache_level, PIN_UPDATE);
4380 if (ret)
4381 return ret;
4382 }
4383 }
4384
4385 list_for_each_entry(vma, &obj->vma_list, vma_link)
4386 vma->node.color = cache_level;
4387 obj->cache_level = cache_level;
4388
4389out:
4390 /* Flush the dirty CPU caches to the backing storage so that the
4391 * object is now coherent at its new cache level (with respect
4392 * to the access domain).
4393 */
4394 if (obj->cache_dirty &&
4395 obj->base.write_domain != I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU &&
4396 cpu_write_needs_clflush(obj)) {
4397 if (i915_gem_clflush_object(obj, true))
4398 i915_gem_chipset_flush(obj->base.dev);
4399 }
4400
4401 return 0;
4402}
4403
4404int i915_gem_get_caching_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
4405 struct drm_file *file)
4406{
4407 struct drm_i915_gem_caching *args = data;
4408 struct drm_gem_object *gobj;
4409 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
4410
4411 gobj = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file, args->handle);
4412 if (gobj == NULL)
4413 return -ENOENT;
4414 obj = to_intel_bo(gobj);
4415
4416 switch (obj->cache_level) {
4417 case I915_CACHE_LLC:
4418 case I915_CACHE_L3_LLC:
4419 args->caching = I915_CACHING_CACHED;
4420 break;
4421
4422 case I915_CACHE_WT:
4423 args->caching = I915_CACHING_DISPLAY;
4424 break;
4425
4426 default:
4427 args->caching = I915_CACHING_NONE;
4428 break;
4429 }
4430
4431 drm_gem_object_unreference_unlocked(&obj->base);
4432 return 0;
4433}
4434
4435int i915_gem_set_caching_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
4436 struct drm_file *file)
4437{
4438 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
4439 struct drm_i915_gem_caching *args = data;
4440 struct drm_gem_object *gobj;
4441 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
4442 enum i915_cache_level level;
4443 int ret;
4444
4445 switch (args->caching) {
4446 case I915_CACHING_NONE:
4447 level = I915_CACHE_NONE;
4448 break;
4449 case I915_CACHING_CACHED:
4450 /*
4451 * Due to a HW issue on BXT A stepping, GPU stores via a
4452 * snooped mapping may leave stale data in a corresponding CPU
4453 * cacheline, whereas normally such cachelines would get
4454 * invalidated.
4455 */
4456 if (IS_BROXTON(dev) && INTEL_REVID(dev) < BXT_REVID_B0)
4457 return -ENODEV;
4458
4459 level = I915_CACHE_LLC;
4460 break;
4461 case I915_CACHING_DISPLAY:
4462 level = HAS_WT(dev) ? I915_CACHE_WT : I915_CACHE_NONE;
4463 break;
4464 default:
4465 return -EINVAL;
4466 }
4467
4468 intel_runtime_pm_get(dev_priv);
4469
4470 ret = i915_mutex_lock_interruptible(dev);
4471 if (ret)
4472 goto rpm_put;
4473
4474 gobj = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file, args->handle);
4475 if (gobj == NULL) {
4476 ret = -ENOENT;
4477 goto unlock;
4478 }
4479 obj = to_intel_bo(gobj);
4480
4481 ret = i915_gem_object_set_cache_level(obj, level);
4482
4483 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
4484unlock:
4485 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
4486rpm_put:
4487 intel_runtime_pm_put(dev_priv);
4488
4489 return ret;
4490}

4492/*
4493 * Prepare buffer for display plane (scanout, cursors, etc).
4494 * Can be called from an uninterruptible phase (modesetting) and allows
4495 * any flushes to be pipelined (for pageflips).
4496 */
4497int
4498i915_gem_object_pin_to_display_plane(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4499 u32 alignment,
4500 struct intel_engine_cs *pipelined,
4501 struct drm_i915_gem_request **pipelined_request,
4502 const struct i915_ggtt_view *view)
4503{
4504 u32 old_read_domains, old_write_domain;
4505 int ret;
4506
4507 ret = i915_gem_object_sync(obj, pipelined, pipelined_request);
4508 if (ret)
4509 return ret;
4510
4511 /* Mark the pin_display early so that we account for the
4512 * display coherency whilst setting up the cache domains.
4513 */
4514 obj->pin_display++;
4515
4516 /* The display engine is not coherent with the LLC cache on gen6. As
4517 * a result, we make sure that the pinning that is about to occur is
4518 * done with uncached PTEs. This is lowest common denominator for all
4519 * chipsets.
4520 *
4521 * However for gen6+, we could do better by using the GFDT bit instead
4522 * of uncaching, which would allow us to flush all the LLC-cached data
4523 * with that bit in the PTE to main memory with just one PIPE_CONTROL.
4524 */
4525 ret = i915_gem_object_set_cache_level(obj,
4526 HAS_WT(obj->base.dev) ? I915_CACHE_WT : I915_CACHE_NONE);
4527 if (ret)
4528 goto err_unpin_display;
4529
4530 /* As the user may map the buffer once pinned in the display plane
4531 * (e.g. libkms for the bootup splash), we have to ensure that we
4532 * always use map_and_fenceable for all scanout buffers.
4533 */
4534 ret = i915_gem_object_ggtt_pin(obj, view, alignment,
4535 view->type == I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL ?
4536 PIN_MAPPABLE : 0);
4537 if (ret)
4538 goto err_unpin_display;
4539
4540 i915_gem_object_flush_cpu_write_domain(obj);
4541
4542 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
4543 old_read_domains = obj->base.read_domains;
4544
4545 /* It should now be out of any other write domains, and we can update
4546 * the domain values for our changes.
4547 */
4548 obj->base.write_domain = 0;
4549 obj->base.read_domains |= I915_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT;
4550
4551 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
4552 old_read_domains,
4553 old_write_domain);
4554
4555 return 0;
4556
4557err_unpin_display:
4558 obj->pin_display--;
4559 return ret;
4560}
4561
4562void
4563i915_gem_object_unpin_from_display_plane(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4564 const struct i915_ggtt_view *view)
4565{
4566 if (WARN_ON(obj->pin_display == 0))
4567 return;
4568
4569 i915_gem_object_ggtt_unpin_view(obj, view);
4570
4571 obj->pin_display--;
4572}

4574/**
4575 * Moves a single object to the CPU read, and possibly write domain.
4576 *
4577 * This function returns when the move is complete, including waiting on
4578 * flushes to occur.
4579 */
4580int
4581i915_gem_object_set_to_cpu_domain(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj, bool write)
4582{
4583 uint32_t old_write_domain, old_read_domains;
4584 int ret;
4585
4586 if (obj->base.write_domain == I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU)
4587 return 0;
4588
4589 ret = i915_gem_object_wait_rendering(obj, !write);
4590 if (ret)
4591 return ret;
4592
4593 i915_gem_object_flush_gtt_write_domain(obj);
4594
4595 old_write_domain = obj->base.write_domain;
4596 old_read_domains = obj->base.read_domains;
4597
4598 /* Flush the CPU cache if it's still invalid. */
4599 if ((obj->base.read_domains & I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU) == 0) {
4600 i915_gem_clflush_object(obj, false);
4601
4602 obj->base.read_domains |= I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU;
4603 }
4604
4605 /* It should now be out of any other write domains, and we can update
4606 * the domain values for our changes.
4607 */
4608 BUG_ON((obj->base.write_domain & ~I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU) != 0);
4609
4610 /* If we're writing through the CPU, then the GPU read domains will
4611 * need to be invalidated at next use.
4612 */
4613 if (write) {
4614 obj->base.read_domains = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU;
4615 obj->base.write_domain = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU;
4616 }
4617
4618 trace_i915_gem_object_change_domain(obj,
4619 old_read_domains,
4620 old_write_domain);
4621
4622 return 0;
4623}
4624
4625/* Throttle our rendering by waiting until the ring has completed our requests
4626 * emitted over 20 msec ago.
4627 *
4628 * Note that if we were to use the current jiffies each time around the loop,
4629 * we wouldn't escape the function with any frames outstanding if the time to
4630 * render a frame was over 20ms.
4631 *
4632 * This should get us reasonable parallelism between CPU and GPU but also
4633 * relatively low latency when blocking on a particular request to finish.
4634 */
4635static int
4636i915_gem_ring_throttle(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *file)
4637{
4638 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
4639 struct drm_i915_file_private *file_priv = file->driver_priv;
4640 unsigned long recent_enough = jiffies - DRM_I915_THROTTLE_JIFFIES;
4641 struct drm_i915_gem_request *request, *target = NULL;
4642 unsigned reset_counter;
4643 int ret;
4644
4645 ret = i915_gem_wait_for_error(&dev_priv->gpu_error);
4646 if (ret)
4647 return ret;
4648
4649 ret = i915_gem_check_wedge(&dev_priv->gpu_error, false);
4650 if (ret)
4651 return ret;
4652
4653 spin_lock(&file_priv->mm.lock);
4654 list_for_each_entry(request, &file_priv->mm.request_list, client_list) {
4655 if (time_after_eq(request->emitted_jiffies, recent_enough))
4656 break;
4657
4658 /*
4659 * Note that the request might not have been submitted yet.
4660 * In which case emitted_jiffies will be zero.
4661 */
4662 if (!request->emitted_jiffies)
4663 continue;
4664
4665 target = request;
4666 }
4667 reset_counter = atomic_read(&dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_counter);
4668 if (target)
4669 i915_gem_request_reference(target);
4670 spin_unlock(&file_priv->mm.lock);
4671
4672 if (target == NULL)
4673 return 0;
4674
4675 ret = __i915_wait_request(target, reset_counter, true, NULL, NULL);
4676 if (ret == 0)
4677 queue_delayed_work(dev_priv->wq, &dev_priv->mm.retire_work, 0);
4678
4679 i915_gem_request_unreference__unlocked(target);
4680
4681 return ret;
4682}
4683
4684static bool
4685i915_vma_misplaced(struct i915_vma *vma, uint32_t alignment, uint64_t flags)
4686{
4687 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj = vma->obj;
4688
4689 if (alignment &&
4690 vma->node.start & (alignment - 1))
4691 return true;
4692
4693 if (flags & PIN_MAPPABLE && !obj->map_and_fenceable)
4694 return true;
4695
4696 if (flags & PIN_OFFSET_BIAS &&
4697 vma->node.start < (flags & PIN_OFFSET_MASK))
4698 return true;
4699
4700 return false;
4701}
4702
4703void __i915_vma_set_map_and_fenceable(struct i915_vma *vma)
4704{
4705 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj = vma->obj;
4706 bool mappable, fenceable;
4707 u32 fence_size, fence_alignment;
4708
4709 fence_size = i915_gem_get_gtt_size(obj->base.dev,
4710 obj->base.size,
4711 obj->tiling_mode);
4712 fence_alignment = i915_gem_get_gtt_alignment(obj->base.dev,
4713 obj->base.size,
4714 obj->tiling_mode,
4715 true);
4716
4717 fenceable = (vma->node.size == fence_size &&
4718 (vma->node.start & (fence_alignment - 1)) == 0);
4719
4720 mappable = (vma->node.start + fence_size <=
4721 to_i915(obj->base.dev)->gtt.mappable_end);
4722
4723 obj->map_and_fenceable = mappable && fenceable;
4724}
4725
4726static int
4727i915_gem_object_do_pin(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4728 struct i915_address_space *vm,
4729 const struct i915_ggtt_view *ggtt_view,
4730 uint32_t alignment,
4731 uint64_t flags)
4732{
4733 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = obj->base.dev->dev_private;
4734 struct i915_vma *vma;
4735 unsigned bound;
4736 int ret;
4737
4738 if (WARN_ON(vm == &dev_priv->mm.aliasing_ppgtt->base))
4739 return -ENODEV;
4740
4741 if (WARN_ON(flags & (PIN_GLOBAL | PIN_MAPPABLE) && !i915_is_ggtt(vm)))
4742 return -EINVAL;
4743
4744 if (WARN_ON((flags & (PIN_MAPPABLE | PIN_GLOBAL)) == PIN_MAPPABLE))
4745 return -EINVAL;
4746
4747 if (WARN_ON(i915_is_ggtt(vm) != !!ggtt_view))
4748 return -EINVAL;
4749
4750 vma = ggtt_view ? i915_gem_obj_to_ggtt_view(obj, ggtt_view) :
4751 i915_gem_obj_to_vma(obj, vm);
4752
4753 if (IS_ERR(vma))
4754 return PTR_ERR(vma);
4755
4756 if (vma) {
4757 if (WARN_ON(vma->pin_count == DRM_I915_GEM_OBJECT_MAX_PIN_COUNT))
4758 return -EBUSY;
4759
4760 if (i915_vma_misplaced(vma, alignment, flags)) {
4761 WARN(vma->pin_count,
4762 "bo is already pinned in %s with incorrect alignment:"
4763 " offset=%08x %08x, req.alignment=%x, req.map_and_fenceable=%d,"
4764 " obj->map_and_fenceable=%d\n",
4765 ggtt_view ? "ggtt" : "ppgtt",
4766 upper_32_bits(vma->node.start),
4767 lower_32_bits(vma->node.start),
4768 alignment,
4769 !!(flags & PIN_MAPPABLE),
4770 obj->map_and_fenceable);
4771 ret = i915_vma_unbind(vma);
4772 if (ret)
4773 return ret;
4774
4775 vma = NULL;
4776 }
4777 }
4778
4779 bound = vma ? vma->bound : 0;
4780 if (vma == NULL || !drm_mm_node_allocated(&vma->node)) {
4781 vma = i915_gem_object_bind_to_vm(obj, vm, ggtt_view, alignment,
4782 flags);
4783 if (IS_ERR(vma))
4784 return PTR_ERR(vma);
4785 } else {
4786 ret = i915_vma_bind(vma, obj->cache_level, flags);
4787 if (ret)
4788 return ret;
4789 }
4790
4791 if (ggtt_view && ggtt_view->type == I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL &&
4792 (bound ^ vma->bound) & GLOBAL_BIND) {
4793 __i915_vma_set_map_and_fenceable(vma);
4794 WARN_ON(flags & PIN_MAPPABLE && !obj->map_and_fenceable);
4795 }
4796
4797 vma->pin_count++;
4798 return 0;
4799}

4838int
4839i915_gem_busy_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
4840 struct drm_file *file)
4841{
4842 struct drm_i915_gem_busy *args = data;
4843 struct drm_gem_object *gobj;
4844 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
4845 int ret;
4846
4847 ret = i915_mutex_lock_interruptible(dev);
4848 if (ret)
4849 return ret;
4850
4851 gobj = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file, args->handle);
4852 if (gobj == NULL) {
4853 ret = -ENOENT;
4854 goto unlock;
4855 }
4856 obj = to_intel_bo(gobj);
4857
4858 /* Count all active objects as busy, even if they are currently not used
4859 * by the gpu. Users of this interface expect objects to eventually
4860 * become non-busy without any further actions, therefore emit any
4861 * necessary flushes here.
4862 */
4863 ret = i915_gem_object_flush_active(obj);
4864 if (ret)
4865 goto unref;
4866
4867 BUILD_BUG_ON(I915_NUM_RINGS > 16);
4868 args->busy = obj->active << 16;
4869 if (obj->last_write_req)
4870 args->busy |= obj->last_write_req->ring->id;
4871
4872unref:
4873 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
4874unlock:
4875 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
4876 return ret;
4877}

4880i915_gem_throttle_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
4881 struct drm_file *file_priv)
4882{

4884}
4885
4886int
4887i915_gem_madvise_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
4888 struct drm_file *file_priv)
4889{
4890 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
4891 struct drm_i915_gem_madvise *args = data;
4892 struct drm_gem_object *gobj;
4893 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
4894 int ret;
4895
4896 switch (args->madv) {
4897 case I915_MADV_DONTNEED:
4898 case I915_MADV_WILLNEED:
4899 break;
4900 default:
4901 return -EINVAL;
4902 }
4903
4904 ret = i915_mutex_lock_interruptible(dev);
4905 if (ret)
4906 return ret;
4907
4908 gobj = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file_priv, args->handle);
4909 if (gobj == NULL) {
4910 ret = -ENOENT;
4911 goto unlock;
4912 }
4913 obj = to_intel_bo(gobj);
4914
4915 if (i915_gem_obj_is_pinned(obj)) {
4916 ret = -EINVAL;
4917 goto out;
4918 }
4919
4920 if (obj->pages &&
4921 obj->tiling_mode != I915_TILING_NONE &&
4922 dev_priv->quirks & QUIRK_PIN_SWIZZLED_PAGES) {
4923 if (obj->madv == I915_MADV_WILLNEED)
4924 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
4925 if (args->madv == I915_MADV_WILLNEED)
4926 i915_gem_object_pin_pages(obj);
4927 }
4928
4929 if (obj->madv != __I915_MADV_PURGED)
4930 obj->madv = args->madv;
4931
4932 /* if the object is no longer attached, discard its backing storage */
4933 if (obj->madv == I915_MADV_DONTNEED && obj->pages == NULL)
4934 i915_gem_object_truncate(obj);
4935
4936 args->retained = obj->madv != __I915_MADV_PURGED;
4937
4938out:
4939 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
4940unlock:
4941 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
4942 return ret;
4943}
4944
4945void i915_gem_object_init(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
4946 const struct drm_i915_gem_object_ops *ops)
4947{
4948 int i;
4949
4950 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&obj->global_list);
4951 for (i = 0; i < I915_NUM_RINGS; i++)
4952 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&obj->ring_list[i]);
4953 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&obj->obj_exec_link);
4954 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&obj->vma_list);
4955 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&obj->batch_pool_link);
4956
4957 obj->ops = ops;
4958
4959 obj->fence_reg = I915_FENCE_REG_NONE;
4960 obj->madv = I915_MADV_WILLNEED;
4961
4962 i915_gem_info_add_obj(obj->base.dev->dev_private, obj->base.size);
4963}
4964
4965static const struct drm_i915_gem_object_ops i915_gem_object_ops = {
4966 .get_pages = i915_gem_object_get_pages_gtt,
4967 .put_pages = i915_gem_object_put_pages_gtt,
4968};
4969
4970struct drm_i915_gem_object *i915_gem_alloc_object(struct drm_device *dev,
4971 size_t size)
4972{
4973#ifdef __NetBSD__
4974 struct drm_i915_private *const dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
4975#endif
4976 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
4977#ifndef __NetBSD__
4978 struct address_space *mapping;
4979 gfp_t mask;
4980#endif
4981
4982 obj = i915_gem_object_alloc(dev);
4983 if (obj == NULL)
4984 return NULL;
4985
4986 if (drm_gem_object_init(dev, &obj->base, size) != 0) {
4987 i915_gem_object_free(obj);
4988 return NULL;
4989 }
4990
4991#ifdef __NetBSD__
4992 uao_set_pgfl(obj->base.filp, dev_priv->gtt.pgfl);
4993#else
4994 mask = GFP_HIGHUSER | __GFP_RECLAIMABLE;
4995 if (IS_CRESTLINE(dev) || IS_BROADWATER(dev)) {
4996 /* 965gm cannot relocate objects above 4GiB. */
4997 mask &= ~__GFP_HIGHMEM;
4998 mask |= __GFP_DMA32;
4999 }
5000
5001 mapping = file_inode(obj->base.filp)->i_mapping;
5002 mapping_set_gfp_mask(mapping, mask);
5003#endif
5004
5005 i915_gem_object_init(obj, &i915_gem_object_ops);
5006
5007 obj->base.write_domain = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU;
5008 obj->base.read_domains = I915_GEM_DOMAIN_CPU;
5009
5010 if (HAS_LLC(dev)) {
5011 /* On some devices, we can have the GPU use the LLC (the CPU
5012 * cache) for about a 10% performance improvement
5013 * compared to uncached. Graphics requests other than
5014 * display scanout are coherent with the CPU in
5015 * accessing this cache. This means in this mode we
5016 * don't need to clflush on the CPU side, and on the
5017 * GPU side we only need to flush internal caches to
5018 * get data visible to the CPU.
5019 *
5020 * However, we maintain the display planes as UC, and so
5021 * need to rebind when first used as such.
5022 */
5023 obj->cache_level = I915_CACHE_LLC;
5024 } else
5025 obj->cache_level = I915_CACHE_NONE;
5026
5027 trace_i915_gem_object_create(obj);
5028
5029 return obj;
5030}
5031
5032static bool discard_backing_storage(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj)
5033{
5034 /* If we are the last user of the backing storage (be it shmemfs
5035 * pages or stolen etc), we know that the pages are going to be
5036 * immediately released. In this case, we can then skip copying
5037 * back the contents from the GPU.
5038 */
5039
5040 if (obj->madv != I915_MADV_WILLNEED)
5041 return false;
5042
5043 if (obj->base.filp == NULL)
5044 return true;
5045
5046 /* At first glance, this looks racy, but then again so would be
5047 * userspace racing mmap against close. However, the first external
5048 * reference to the filp can only be obtained through the
5049 * i915_gem_mmap_ioctl() which safeguards us against the user
5050 * acquiring such a reference whilst we are in the middle of
5051 * freeing the object.
5052 */
5053#ifdef __NetBSD__
5054 /* XXX This number might be a fencepost. */
5055 return obj->base.filp->uo_refs == 1;
5056#else
5057 return atomic_long_read(&obj->base.filp->f_count) == 1;
5058#endif
5059}
5060
5061void i915_gem_free_object(struct drm_gem_object *gem_obj)
5062{
5063 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj = to_intel_bo(gem_obj);
5064 struct drm_device *dev = obj->base.dev;
5065 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5066 struct i915_vma *vma, *next;
5067
5068 intel_runtime_pm_get(dev_priv);
5069
5070 trace_i915_gem_object_destroy(obj);
5071
5072 list_for_each_entry_safe(vma, next, &obj->vma_list, vma_link) {
5073 int ret;
5074
5075 vma->pin_count = 0;
5076 ret = i915_vma_unbind(vma);
5077 if (WARN_ON(ret == -ERESTARTSYS)) {
5078 bool was_interruptible;
5079
5080 was_interruptible = dev_priv->mm.interruptible;
5081 dev_priv->mm.interruptible = false;
5082
5083 WARN_ON(i915_vma_unbind(vma));
5084
5085 dev_priv->mm.interruptible = was_interruptible;
5086 }
5087 }
5088
5089 /* Stolen objects don't hold a ref, but do hold pin count. Fix that up
5090 * before progressing. */
5091 if (obj->stolen)
5092 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
5093
5094 WARN_ON(obj->frontbuffer_bits);
5095
5096 if (obj->pages && obj->madv == I915_MADV_WILLNEED &&
5097 dev_priv->quirks & QUIRK_PIN_SWIZZLED_PAGES &&
5098 obj->tiling_mode != I915_TILING_NONE)
5099 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
5100
5101 if (WARN_ON(obj->pages_pin_count))
5102 obj->pages_pin_count = 0;
5103 if (discard_backing_storage(obj))
5104 obj->madv = I915_MADV_DONTNEED;
5105 i915_gem_object_put_pages(obj);
5106 i915_gem_object_free_mmap_offset(obj);
5107
5108 BUG_ON(obj->pages);
5109
5110 if (obj->base.import_attach)
5111 drm_prime_gem_destroy(&obj->base, NULL);
5112
5113 if (obj->ops->release)
5114 obj->ops->release(obj);
5115
5116 drm_gem_object_release(&obj->base);
5117 i915_gem_info_remove_obj(dev_priv, obj->base.size);
5118
5119 kfree(obj->bit_17);
5120 i915_gem_object_free(obj);
5121
5122 intel_runtime_pm_put(dev_priv);
5123}

5125struct i915_vma *i915_gem_obj_to_vma(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj,
5126 struct i915_address_space *vm)
5127{
5128 struct i915_vma *vma;
5129 list_for_each_entry(vma, &obj->vma_list, vma_link) {
5130 if (i915_is_ggtt(vma->vm) &&
5131 vma->ggtt_view.type != I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL)
5132 continue;
5133 if (vma->vm == vm)
5134 return vma;
5135 }
5136 return NULL;

5141{

5143 struct i915_vma *vma;

5146 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
5147
5148 list_for_each_entry(vma, &obj->vma_list, vma_link)
5149 if (vma->vm == ggtt &&
5150 i915_ggtt_view_equal(&vma->ggtt_view, view))

5154
5155void i915_gem_vma_destroy(struct i915_vma *vma)
5156{
5157 struct i915_address_space *vm = NULL;
5158 WARN_ON(vma->node.allocated);
5159
5160 /* Keep the vma as a placeholder in the execbuffer reservation lists */
5161 if (!list_empty(&vma->exec_list))
5162 return;
5163
5164 vm = vma->vm;
5165
5166 if (!i915_is_ggtt(vm))
5167 i915_ppgtt_put(i915_vm_to_ppgtt(vm));
5168
5169 list_del(&vma->vma_link);
5170
5171 kmem_cache_free(to_i915(vma->obj->base.dev)->vmas, vma);
5172}

5185int
5186i915_gem_suspend(struct drm_device *dev)
5187{
5188 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5189 int ret = 0;
5190
5191 mutex_lock(&dev->struct_mutex);
5192 ret = i915_gpu_idle(dev);
5193 if (ret)
5194 goto err;
5195
5196 i915_gem_retire_requests(dev);
5197
5198 i915_gem_stop_ringbuffers(dev);
5199 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
5200
5201 cancel_delayed_work_sync(&dev_priv->gpu_error.hangcheck_work);
5202 cancel_delayed_work_sync(&dev_priv->mm.retire_work);
5203 flush_delayed_work(&dev_priv->mm.idle_work);
5204
5205 /* Assert that we sucessfully flushed all the work and
5206 * reset the GPU back to its idle, low power state.
5207 */
5208 WARN_ON(dev_priv->mm.busy);
5209
5210 return 0;
5211
5212err:
5213 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
5214 return ret;
5215}
5216
5217int i915_gem_l3_remap(struct drm_i915_gem_request *req, int slice)
5218{
5219 struct intel_engine_cs *ring = req->ring;
5220 struct drm_device *dev = ring->dev;
5221 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5222 u32 reg_base = GEN7_L3LOG_BASE + (slice * 0x200);
5223 u32 *remap_info = dev_priv->l3_parity.remap_info[slice];
5224 int i, ret;
5225
5226 if (!HAS_L3_DPF(dev) || !remap_info)
5227 return 0;
5228
5229 ret = intel_ring_begin(req, GEN7_L3LOG_SIZE / 4 * 3);
5230 if (ret)
5231 return ret;
5232
5233 /*
5234 * Note: We do not worry about the concurrent register cacheline hang
5235 * here because no other code should access these registers other than
5236 * at initialization time.
5237 */
5238 for (i = 0; i < GEN7_L3LOG_SIZE; i += 4) {
5239 intel_ring_emit(ring, MI_LOAD_REGISTER_IMM(1));
5240 intel_ring_emit(ring, reg_base + i);
5241 intel_ring_emit(ring, remap_info[i/4]);
5242 }
5243
5244 intel_ring_advance(ring);
5245
5246 return ret;
5247}
5248
5249void i915_gem_init_swizzling(struct drm_device *dev)
5250{
5251 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5252
5253 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 5 ||
5254 dev_priv->mm.bit_6_swizzle_x == I915_BIT_6_SWIZZLE_NONE)
5255 return;
5256
5257 I915_WRITE(DISP_ARB_CTL, I915_READ(DISP_ARB_CTL) |
5258 DISP_TILE_SURFACE_SWIZZLING);
5259
5260 if (IS_GEN5(dev))
5261 return;
5262
5263 I915_WRITE(TILECTL, I915_READ(TILECTL) | TILECTL_SWZCTL);
5264 if (IS_GEN6(dev))
5265 I915_WRITE(ARB_MODE, _MASKED_BIT_ENABLE(ARB_MODE_SWIZZLE_SNB));
5266 else if (IS_GEN7(dev))
5267 I915_WRITE(ARB_MODE, _MASKED_BIT_ENABLE(ARB_MODE_SWIZZLE_IVB));
5268 else if (IS_GEN8(dev))
5269 I915_WRITE(GAMTARBMODE, _MASKED_BIT_ENABLE(ARB_MODE_SWIZZLE_BDW));
5270 else
5271 BUG();
5272}

5347
5348int
5349i915_gem_init_hw(struct drm_device *dev)
5350{
5351 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5352 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
5353 int ret, i, j;
5354
5355 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 6 && !intel_enable_gtt())
5356 return -EIO;
5357
5358 /* Double layer security blanket, see i915_gem_init() */
5359 intel_uncore_forcewake_get(dev_priv, FORCEWAKE_ALL);
5360
5361 if (dev_priv->ellc_size)
5362 I915_WRITE(HSW_IDICR, I915_READ(HSW_IDICR) | IDIHASHMSK(0xf));
5363
5364 if (IS_HASWELL(dev))
5365 I915_WRITE(MI_PREDICATE_RESULT_2, IS_HSW_GT3(dev) ?
5366 LOWER_SLICE_ENABLED : LOWER_SLICE_DISABLED);
5367
5368 if (HAS_PCH_NOP(dev)) {
5369 if (IS_IVYBRIDGE(dev)) {
5370 u32 temp = I915_READ(GEN7_MSG_CTL);
5371 temp &= ~(WAIT_FOR_PCH_FLR_ACK | WAIT_FOR_PCH_RESET_ACK);
5372 I915_WRITE(GEN7_MSG_CTL, temp);
5373 } else if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 7) {
5374 u32 temp = I915_READ(HSW_NDE_RSTWRN_OPT);
5375 temp &= ~RESET_PCH_HANDSHAKE_ENABLE;
5376 I915_WRITE(HSW_NDE_RSTWRN_OPT, temp);
5377 }
5378 }
5379
5380 i915_gem_init_swizzling(dev);
5381
5382 /*
5383 * At least 830 can leave some of the unused rings
5384 * "active" (ie. head != tail) after resume which
5385 * will prevent c3 entry. Makes sure all unused rings
5386 * are totally idle.
5387 */
5388 init_unused_rings(dev);
5389
5390 BUG_ON(!dev_priv->ring[RCS].default_context);
5391
5392 ret = i915_ppgtt_init_hw(dev);
5393 if (ret) {
5394 DRM_ERROR("PPGTT enable HW failed %d\n", ret);
5395 goto out;
5396 }
5397
5398 /* Need to do basic initialisation of all rings first: */
5399 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
5400 ret = ring->init_hw(ring);
5401 if (ret)
5402 goto out;
5403 }
5404
5405 /* We can't enable contexts until all firmware is loaded */
5406 if (HAS_GUC_UCODE(dev)) {
5407 ret = intel_guc_ucode_load(dev);
5408 if (ret) {
5409 /*
5410 * If we got an error and GuC submission is enabled, map
5411 * the error to -EIO so the GPU will be declared wedged.
5412 * OTOH, if we didn't intend to use the GuC anyway, just
5413 * discard the error and carry on.
5414 */
5415 DRM_ERROR("Failed to initialize GuC, error %d%s\n", ret,
5416 i915.enable_guc_submission ? "" :
5417 " (ignored)");
5418 ret = i915.enable_guc_submission ? -EIO : 0;
5419 if (ret)
5420 goto out;
5421 }
5422 }
5423
5424 /*
5425 * Increment the next seqno by 0x100 so we have a visible break
5426 * on re-initialisation
5427 */
5428 ret = i915_gem_set_seqno(dev, dev_priv->next_seqno+0x100);
5429 if (ret)
5430 goto out;
5431
5432 /* Now it is safe to go back round and do everything else: */
5433 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i) {
5434 struct drm_i915_gem_request *req;
5435
5436 WARN_ON(!ring->default_context);
5437
5438 ret = i915_gem_request_alloc(ring, ring->default_context, &req);
5439 if (ret) {
5440 i915_gem_cleanup_ringbuffer(dev);
5441 goto out;
5442 }
5443
5444 if (ring->id == RCS) {
5445 for (j = 0; j < NUM_L3_SLICES(dev); j++)
5446 i915_gem_l3_remap(req, j);
5447 }
5448
5449 ret = i915_ppgtt_init_ring(req);
5450 if (ret && ret != -EIO) {
5451 DRM_ERROR("PPGTT enable ring #%d failed %d\n", i, ret);
5452 i915_gem_request_cancel(req);
5453 i915_gem_cleanup_ringbuffer(dev);
5454 goto out;
5455 }
5456
5457 ret = i915_gem_context_enable(req);
5458 if (ret && ret != -EIO) {
5459 DRM_ERROR("Context enable ring #%d failed %d\n", i, ret);
5460 i915_gem_request_cancel(req);
5461 i915_gem_cleanup_ringbuffer(dev);
5462 goto out;
5463 }
5464
5465 i915_add_request_no_flush(req);
5466 }
5467
5468out:
5469 intel_uncore_forcewake_put(dev_priv, FORCEWAKE_ALL);
5470 return ret;
5471}
5472
5473int i915_gem_init(struct drm_device *dev)
5474{
5475 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5476 int ret;
5477
5478 i915.enable_execlists = intel_sanitize_enable_execlists(dev,
5479 i915.enable_execlists);
5480
5481 idr_preload(GFP_KERNEL); /* gem context */
5482 mutex_lock(&dev->struct_mutex);
5483
5484 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
5485 /* VLVA0 (potential hack), BIOS isn't actually waking us */
5486 I915_WRITE(VLV_GTLC_WAKE_CTRL, VLV_GTLC_ALLOWWAKEREQ);
5487 if (wait_for((I915_READ(VLV_GTLC_PW_STATUS) &
5488 VLV_GTLC_ALLOWWAKEACK), 10))
5489 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("allow wake ack timed out\n");
5490 }
5491
5492 if (!i915.enable_execlists) {
5493 dev_priv->gt.execbuf_submit = i915_gem_ringbuffer_submission;
5494 dev_priv->gt.init_rings = i915_gem_init_rings;
5495 dev_priv->gt.cleanup_ring = intel_cleanup_ring_buffer;
5496 dev_priv->gt.stop_ring = intel_stop_ring_buffer;
5497 } else {
5498 dev_priv->gt.execbuf_submit = intel_execlists_submission;
5499 dev_priv->gt.init_rings = intel_logical_rings_init;
5500 dev_priv->gt.cleanup_ring = intel_logical_ring_cleanup;
5501 dev_priv->gt.stop_ring = intel_logical_ring_stop;
5502 }
5503
5504 /* This is just a security blanket to placate dragons.
5505 * On some systems, we very sporadically observe that the first TLBs
5506 * used by the CS may be stale, despite us poking the TLB reset. If
5507 * we hold the forcewake during initialisation these problems
5508 * just magically go away.
5509 */
5510 intel_uncore_forcewake_get(dev_priv, FORCEWAKE_ALL);
5511
5512 ret = i915_gem_init_userptr(dev);
5513 if (ret)
5514 goto out_unlock;
5515
5516 i915_gem_init_global_gtt(dev);
5517
5518 ret = i915_gem_context_init(dev);
5519 if (ret)
5520 goto out_unlock;
5521
5522 ret = dev_priv->gt.init_rings(dev);
5523 if (ret)
5524 goto out_unlock;
5525
5526 ret = i915_gem_init_hw(dev);
5527 if (ret == -EIO) {
5528 /* Allow ring initialisation to fail by marking the GPU as
5529 * wedged. But we only want to do this where the GPU is angry,
5530 * for all other failure, such as an allocation failure, bail.
5531 */
5532 DRM_ERROR("Failed to initialize GPU, declaring it wedged\n");
5533 atomic_or(I915_WEDGED, &dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_counter);
5534 ret = 0;
5535 }
5536
5537out_unlock:
5538 intel_uncore_forcewake_put(dev_priv, FORCEWAKE_ALL);
5539 mutex_unlock(&dev->struct_mutex);
5540 idr_preload_end();
5541
5542 return ret;
5543}

5545void
5546i915_gem_cleanup_ringbuffer(struct drm_device *dev)
5547{
5548 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5549 struct intel_engine_cs *ring;
5550 int i;
5551
5552 for_each_ring(ring, dev_priv, i)
5553 dev_priv->gt.cleanup_ring(ring);
5554
5555 if (i915.enable_execlists)
5556 /*
5557 * Neither the BIOS, ourselves or any other kernel
5558 * expects the system to be in execlists mode on startup,
5559 * so we need to reset the GPU back to legacy mode.
5560 */
5561 intel_gpu_reset(dev);
5562}

5565init_ring_lists(struct intel_engine_cs *ring)
5566{
5567 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ring->active_list);
5568 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ring->request_list);
5569}

5571void
5572i915_gem_load(struct drm_device *dev)
5573{
5574 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5575 int i;
5576
5577 dev_priv->objects =
5578 kmem_cache_create("i915_gem_object",
5579 sizeof(struct drm_i915_gem_object), 0,
5580 SLAB_HWCACHE_ALIGN,
5581 NULL);
5582 dev_priv->vmas =
5583 kmem_cache_create("i915_gem_vma",
5584 sizeof(struct i915_vma), 0,
5585 SLAB_HWCACHE_ALIGN,
5586 NULL);
5587 dev_priv->requests =
5588 kmem_cache_create("i915_gem_request",
5589 sizeof(struct drm_i915_gem_request), 0,
5590 SLAB_HWCACHE_ALIGN,
5591 NULL);
5592
5593 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->vm_list);
5594 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->context_list);
5595 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->mm.unbound_list);
5596 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->mm.bound_list);
5597 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->mm.fence_list);
5598 for (i = 0; i < I915_NUM_RINGS; i++)
5599 init_ring_lists(&dev_priv->ring[i]);
5600 for (i = 0; i < I915_MAX_NUM_FENCES; i++)
5601 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->fence_regs[i].lru_list);
5602 INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&dev_priv->mm.retire_work,
5603 i915_gem_retire_work_handler);
5604 INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&dev_priv->mm.idle_work,
5605 i915_gem_idle_work_handler);
5606#ifdef __NetBSD__
5607 spin_lock_init(&dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_lock);
5608 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_queue, "i915errst");
5609#else
5610 init_waitqueue_head(&dev_priv->gpu_error.reset_queue);
5611#endif
5612
5613 dev_priv->relative_constants_mode = I915_EXEC_CONSTANTS_REL_GENERAL;
5614
5615 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 7 && !IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
5616 dev_priv->num_fence_regs = 32;
5617 else if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 4 || IS_I945G(dev) || IS_I945GM(dev) || IS_G33(dev))
5618 dev_priv->num_fence_regs = 16;
5619 else
5620 dev_priv->num_fence_regs = 8;
5621
5622 if (intel_vgpu_active(dev))
5623 dev_priv->num_fence_regs =
5624 I915_READ(vgtif_reg(avail_rs.fence_num));
5625
5626 /*
5627 * Set initial sequence number for requests.
5628 * Using this number allows the wraparound to happen early,
5629 * catching any obvious problems.
5630 */
5631 dev_priv->next_seqno = ((u32)~0 - 0x1100);
5632 dev_priv->last_seqno = ((u32)~0 - 0x1101);
5633
5634 /* Initialize fence registers to zero */
5635 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev_priv->mm.fence_list);
5636 i915_gem_restore_fences(dev);
5637
5638 i915_gem_detect_bit_6_swizzle(dev);
5639#ifdef __NetBSD__
5640 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&dev_priv->pending_flip_queue, "i915flip");
5641 spin_lock_init(&dev_priv->pending_flip_lock);
5642#else
5643 init_waitqueue_head(&dev_priv->pending_flip_queue);
5644#endif
5645
5646 dev_priv->mm.interruptible = true;
5647
5648 i915_gem_shrinker_init(dev_priv);
5649#ifdef __NetBSD__
5650 linux_mutex_init(&dev_priv->fb_tracking.lock);
5651#else
5652 mutex_init(&dev_priv->fb_tracking.lock);
5653#endif
5654}
5655
5656void i915_gem_release(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *file)
5657{
5658 struct drm_i915_file_private *file_priv = file->driver_priv;
5659
5660 /* Clean up our request list when the client is going away, so that
5661 * later retire_requests won't dereference our soon-to-be-gone
5662 * file_priv.
5663 */
5664 spin_lock(&file_priv->mm.lock);
5665 while (!list_empty(&file_priv->mm.request_list)) {
5666 struct drm_i915_gem_request *request;
5667
5668 request = list_first_entry(&file_priv->mm.request_list,
5669 struct drm_i915_gem_request,
5670 client_list);
5671 list_del(&request->client_list);
5672 request->file_priv = NULL;
5673 }
5674 spin_unlock(&file_priv->mm.lock);
5675
5676 if (!list_empty(&file_priv->rps.link)) {
5677 spin_lock(&to_i915(dev)->rps.client_lock);
5678 list_del(&file_priv->rps.link);
5679 spin_unlock(&to_i915(dev)->rps.client_lock);
5680 }
5681}

5683int i915_gem_open(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *file)
5684{
5685 struct drm_i915_file_private *file_priv;
5686 int ret;
5687
5688 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("\n");
5689
5690 file_priv = kzalloc(sizeof(*file_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
5691 if (!file_priv)
5692 return -ENOMEM;
5693
5694 file->driver_priv = file_priv;
5695 file_priv->dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5696 file_priv->file = file;
5697 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&file_priv->rps.link);
5698
5699 spin_lock_init(&file_priv->mm.lock);
5700 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&file_priv->mm.request_list);
5701
5702 ret = i915_gem_context_open(dev, file);
5703 if (ret)
5704 kfree(file_priv);
5705
5706 return ret;
5707}

5709/**
5710 * i915_gem_track_fb - update frontbuffer tracking
5711 * @old: current GEM buffer for the frontbuffer slots
5712 * @new: new GEM buffer for the frontbuffer slots
5713 * @frontbuffer_bits: bitmask of frontbuffer slots
5714 *
5715 * This updates the frontbuffer tracking bits @frontbuffer_bits by clearing them
5716 * from @old and setting them in @new. Both @old and @new can be NULL.
5717 */
5718void i915_gem_track_fb(struct drm_i915_gem_object *old,
5719 struct drm_i915_gem_object *new,
5720 unsigned frontbuffer_bits)
5721{
5722 if (old) {
5723 WARN_ON(!mutex_is_locked(&old->base.dev->struct_mutex));
5724 WARN_ON(!(old->frontbuffer_bits & frontbuffer_bits));
5725 old->frontbuffer_bits &= ~frontbuffer_bits;
5726 }
5727
5728 if (new) {
5729 WARN_ON(!mutex_is_locked(&new->base.dev->struct_mutex));
5730 WARN_ON(new->frontbuffer_bits & frontbuffer_bits);
5731 new->frontbuffer_bits |= frontbuffer_bits;
5732 }
5733}

5735/* All the new VM stuff */
5736u64 i915_gem_obj_offset(struct drm_i915_gem_object *o,
5737 struct i915_address_space *vm)
5738{
5739 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = o->base.dev->dev_private;
5740 struct i915_vma *vma;
5741
5742 WARN_ON(vm == &dev_priv->mm.aliasing_ppgtt->base);
5743
5744 list_for_each_entry(vma, &o->vma_list, vma_link) {
5745 if (i915_is_ggtt(vma->vm) &&
5746 vma->ggtt_view.type != I915_GGTT_VIEW_NORMAL)
5747 continue;
5748 if (vma->vm == vm)
5749 return vma->node.start;
5750 }
5751
5752 WARN(1, "%s vma for this object not found.\n",
5753 i915_is_ggtt(vm) ? "global" : "ppgtt");
5754 return -1;
5755}

5757u64 i915_gem_obj_ggtt_offset_view(struct drm_i915_gem_object *o,
5758 const struct i915_ggtt_view *view)
5759{
5760 struct i915_address_space *ggtt = i915_obj_to_ggtt(o);
5761 struct i915_vma *vma;
5762
5763 list_for_each_entry(vma, &o->vma_list, vma_link)
5764 if (vma->vm == ggtt &&
5765 i915_ggtt_view_equal(&vma->ggtt_view, view))
5766 return vma->node.start;
5767
5768 WARN(1, "global vma for this object not found. (view=%u)\n", view->type);
5769 return -1;
5770}

5844/* Allocate a new GEM object and fill it with the supplied data */
5845struct drm_i915_gem_object *
5846i915_gem_object_create_from_data(struct drm_device *dev,
5847 const void *data, size_t size)
5848{
5849 struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
5850#ifdef __NetBSD__
5851 struct iovec iov = { .iov_base = __UNCONST(data), .iov_len = size };
5852 struct uio uio = {
5853 .uio_iov = &iov,
5854 .uio_iovcnt = 1,
5855 .uio_offset = 0,
5856 .uio_resid = size,
5857 .uio_rw = UIO_WRITE,
5858 };
5859#else
5860 struct sg_table *sg;
5861#endif
5862 size_t bytes;
5863 int ret;
5864
5865 obj = i915_gem_alloc_object(dev, round_up(size, PAGE_SIZE));
5866 if (IS_ERR_OR_NULL(obj))
5867 return obj;
5868
5869 ret = i915_gem_object_set_to_cpu_domain(obj, true);
5870 if (ret)
5871 goto fail;
5872
5873 ret = i915_gem_object_get_pages(obj);
5874 if (ret)
5875 goto fail;
5876
5877 i915_gem_object_pin_pages(obj);
5878#ifdef __NetBSD__
5879 UIO_SETUP_SYSSPACE(&uio);
5880 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
5881 ret = -ubc_uiomove(obj->base.filp, &uio, size, UVM_ADV_NORMAL,
5882 UBC_WRITE);
5883 if (ret)
5884 goto fail;
5885 bytes = size - uio.uio_resid;
5886#else
5887 sg = obj->pages;
5888 bytes = sg_copy_from_buffer(sg->sgl, sg->nents, (void *)data, size);
5889#endif
5890 i915_gem_object_unpin_pages(obj);
5891
5892 if (WARN_ON(bytes != size)) {
5893 DRM_ERROR("Incomplete copy, wrote %zu of %zu", bytes, size);
5894 ret = -EFAULT;
5895 goto fail;
5896 }
5897
5898 return obj;
5899
5900fail:
5901 drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
5902 return ERR_PTR(ret);
5903}
